cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.GT, cs.SY, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
1. cs.IT (Information Theory): The paper focuses on deriving the coverage probability and spectral efficiency of a worst-case mobile user in a downlink cellular network, which involves analyzing the information transmission and channel capacity. 
2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture): The paper deals with the performance analysis of a mobile user in a cellular network, which falls under the scope of networking and internet architecture. 
3. cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory): The paper uses stochastic geometry to model the cellular network, which involves concepts from game theory such as strategic decision-making and optimization. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper investigates the impact of coordinated scheduling on the performance of the worst-case mobile user, which involves control and optimization of the network system. 
5. cs.MM (Multimedia): The paper discusses the spectral efficiency of the worst-case mobile user, which is related to the transmission and processing of multimedia data in the network.
